cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.CR, cs.MM 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with wireless content delivery and caching in an online social network setting. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper considers the energy cost of downloading data over a time-varying wireless channel. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the paper proposes a proactive caching scheme to reduce energy consumption, which can be seen as a control problem. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is less likely but still possible as the paper may touch upon security concerns related to content caching. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is also less likely but possible as the paper deals with content delivery and consumption.
